{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887658504,"sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2728bc001enRuz8j2j8KIDP","messageID":"msg_d7b2711b4001lhAz91H4OoUalX","sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2baa552920bd44f4a22455ed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-037.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-037.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** example  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: \n9: **Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n14: \n15: ### REQ-037.1: PCAP 分析器基础功能\n16: \n17: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 提供一个 PCAP 分析器脚本，能够解析 PCAP 文件并提取基本统计信息。\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: 解析 PCAP 文件\n20: - **GIVEN** 一个有效的 PCAP 文件路径\n21: - **WHEN** 运行 PCAP 分析器\n22: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出数据包总数、协议分布、时间范围\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: 处理无效文件\n25: - **GIVEN** 一个不存在或无效的 PCAP 文件\n26: - **WHEN** 运行 PCAP 分析器\n27: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 抛出 `FileNotFoundError` 或解析错误并输出有意义的错误信息\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: 空文件处理\n30: - **GIVEN** 一个空的或无数据包的 PCAP 文件\n31: - **WHEN** 运行分析器\n32: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出零统计并提示文件无有效数据\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### REQ-037.2: 协议统计\n37: \n38: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 按协议类型统计数据包数量。\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: TCP/UDP/HTTP 统计\n41: - **GIVEN** 包含多种协议的 PCAP 文件\n42: - **WHEN** 分析器执行协议统计\n43: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出每种协议的数据包数量和占比\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: 协议分层统计\n46: - **GIVEN** 包含多层协议的 PCAP 文件 (如 Ethernet/IP/TCP/HTTP)\n47: - **WHEN** 分析器执行协议统计\n48: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 按层级输出各层协议分布\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### REQ-037.3: 流量分析\n53: \n54: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 提供流量分析功能，包括源/目的 IP 统计。\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Top N IP 地址\n57: - **GIVEN** 包含多个 IP 地址的 PCAP 文件\n58: - **WHEN** 请求 Top N 源/目的 IP\n59: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 按数据包数量排序返回 Top N IP 地址\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: 流量时间分布\n62: - **GIVEN** 包含时间跨度的 PCAP 文件\n63: - **WHEN** 分析流量时间分布\n64: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出每秒/每分钟的数据包速率\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: 端口统计\n67: - **GIVEN** 包含 TCP/UDP 端口的 PCAP 文件\n68: - **WHEN** 分析端口分布\n69: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出最常用的源/目的端口\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ### REQ-037.4: AgentCube SDK 集成\n74: \n75: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 使用 `agentcube-sdk` 执行 PCAP 分析。\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient 使用\n78: - **GIVEN** AgentCube SDK 已安装并配置\n79: - **WHEN** 通过 `CodeInterpreterClient` 执行 PCAP 分析脚本\n80: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 返回分析结果\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: 文件上传与下载\n83: - **GIVEN** 本地 PCAP 文件\n84: - **WHEN** 使用 `upload_file` 上传到远程环境\n85: - **THEN** 文件 SHALL 成功上传并可被分析脚本访问\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: 分析结果导出\n88: - **GIVEN** PCAP 分析完成\n89: - **WHEN** 调用 `download_file` 获取结果\n90: - **THEN** 结果文件 SHALL 包含完整的分析数据\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: 会话清理\n93: - **GIVEN** 使用上下文管理器创建 CodeInterpreterClient\n94: - **WHEN** with 块退出\n95: - **THEN** 会话 SHALL 被正确清理，临时文件被删除\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### REQ-037.5: 示例脚本结构\n100: \n101: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 提供示例脚本 `examples/pcap_analyzer.py`。\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: 命令行参数\n104: - **GIVEN** 用户在命令行提供 PCAP 文件路径\n105: - **WHEN** 运行示例脚本\n106: - **THEN** 脚本 SHALL 接受 `--file`, `--top-n`, `--output` 参数\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: 输出格式\n109: - **GIVEN** 分析完成\n110: - **WHEN** 输出结果\n111: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 支持 JSON 和文本两种输出格式\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: 详细模式\n114: - **GIVEN** 用户指定 `--verbose` 标志\n115: - **WHEN** 运行分析器\n116: - **THEN** 系统 SHALL 输出详细的调试信息\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ### REQ-037.6: 依赖管理\n121: \n122: **Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 定义 PCAP 分析所需的 Python 依赖。\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: scapy 安装\n125: - **GIVEN** 示例应用需要解析 PCAP 文件\n126: - **WHEN** 初始化环境\n127: - **THEN** scapy 库 SHALL 被安装\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: 可选依赖\n130: - **GIVEN** 用户需要高级可视化功能\n131: - **WHEN** 安装可选依赖\n132: - **THEN** matplotlib 等可视化库 SHALL 可安装\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Data Types\n137: \n138: ```python\n139: # PCAP 分析结果结构\n140: class PcapAnalysisResult(TypedDict, total=False):\n141:     total_packets: int\n142:     duration_seconds: float\n143:     protocols: Dict[str, int]  # protocol -> count\n144:     top_src_ips: List[Tuple[str, int]]  # (ip, count)\n145:     top_dst_ips: List[Tuple[str, int]]\n146:     top_src_ports: List[Tuple[int, int]]\n147:     top_dst_ports: List[Tuple[int, int]]\n148:     packets_per_second: float\n149:     start_time: str\n150:     end_time: str\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## CLI Flags Summary\n156: \n157: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n158: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n159: | `--file` | `-f` | str | Required | PCAP 文件路径 |\n160: | `--top-n` | `-n` | int | 10 | Top N IP/端口数量 |\n161: | `--output` | `-o` | str | None | 输出文件路径 |\n162: | `--format` | - | str | \"text\" | 输出格式：text 或 json |\n163: | `--verbose` | `-v` | bool | False | 详细模式 |\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Dependencies\n168: \n169: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n170: |---------|---------|---------|\n171: | `scapy` | >=2.5.0 | PCAP 解析 |\n172: | `agentcube-sdk` | >=0.1.0 | AgentCube 客户端 |\n173: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | 配置处理 |\n174: | `matplotlib` | >=3.7.0 | 可视化 (可选) |\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ## Acceptance Checklist\n179: \n180: - [ ] `examples/pcap_analyzer.py` — 主分析脚本实现\n181: - [ ] PCAP 文件解析功能 (使用 scapy)\n182: - [ ] 协议统计分析\n183: - [ ] IP/端口统计功能\n184: - [ ] AgentCube SDK 集成示例\n185: - [ ] 命令行参数解析\n186: - [ ] JSON/文本输出支持\n187: - [ ] 错误处理与验证\n188: - [ ] 依赖配置文件 (requirements.txt)\n189: - [ ] 使用文档/示例\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ## Open Questions\n194: \n195: 1. 是否需要支持实时 PCAP 流分析？\n196: 2. 是否需要支持 PCAPng 格式？\n197: 3. 是否需要生成可视化图表 (如时间序列图、协议分布饼图)？\n198: 4. 是否需要导出为标准报告格式 (PDF/HTML)？\n\n(End of file - total 198 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n**Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-037.1: PCAP 分析器基础功能\n\n**Requirement:** 系统 SHALL 提供一个 PCAP 分析器脚本，能够解析 PCAP 文件并提取基本统计信息。\n\n#### Scenario: 解析 PCAP 文件\n- **GIVEN** 一个有效的 PCAP 文件路径","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-037.md","time":{"start":1775887658490,"end":1775887658502}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887658510,"sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b271e5b001Pb2gjsrO0HWKMp","messageID":"msg_d7b2711b4001lhAz91H4OoUalX","sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b9a03dfc5dbf4db3b0001339","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer - Parse PCAP files and extract network traffic statistics.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import json\n4: import sys\n5: from collections import Counter\n6: from datetime import datetime\n7: from pathlib import Path\n8: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\n9: \n10: import typer\n11: from scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, rdpcap\n12: from scapy.layers.http import HTTPRequest, HTTPResponse\n13: \n14: app = typer.Typer()\n15: \n16: \n17: class PcapAnalysisError(Exception):\n18:     \"\"\"Custom exception for PCAP analysis errors.\"\"\"\n19: \n20:     pass\n21: \n22: \n23: def parse_pcap(file_path: str) -> Any:\n24:     \"\"\"Parse a PCAP file and return packets.\n25: \n26:     Args:\n27:         file_path: Path to the PCAP file\n28: \n29:     Returns:\n30:         List of packets from the PCAP file\n31: \n32:     Raises:\n33:         FileNotFoundError: If the PCAP file does not exist\n34:         PcapAnalysisError: If the file cannot be parsed\n35:     \"\"\"\n36:     path = Path(file_path)\n37:     if not path.exists():\n38:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"PCAP file not found: {file_path}\")\n39: \n40:     try:\n41:         packets = rdpcap(file_path)\n42:         return packets\n43:     except Exception as e:\n44:         raise PcapAnalysisError(f\"Failed to parse PCAP file: {e}\")\n45: \n46: \n47: def get_packet_protocol(packet: Any) -> str:\n48:     \"\"\"Extract the protocol from a packet.\n49: \n50:     Args:\n51:         packet: Scapy packet object\n52: \n53:     Returns:\n54:         Protocol name as string\n55:     \"\"\"\n56:     if packet.haslayer(HTTPRequest):\n57:         return \"HTTP\"\n58:     elif packet.haslayer(HTTPResponse):\n59:         return \"HTTP\"\n60:     elif packet.haslayer(TCP):\n61:         return \"TCP\"\n62:     elif packet.haslayer(UDP):\n63:         return \"UDP\"\n64:     elif packet.haslayer(IP):\n65:         return \"IP\"\n66:     else:\n67:         return \"OTHER\"\n68: \n69: \n70: def analyze_packets(packets: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n71:     \"\"\"Analyze packets and return statistics.\n72: \n73:     Args:\n74:         packets: List of scapy packets\n75: \n76:     Returns:\n77:         Dictionary containing analysis results\n78:     \"\"\"\n79:     if len(packets) == 0:\n80:         return {\n81:             \"total_packets\": 0,\n82:             \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n83:             \"protocols\": {},\n84:             \"top_src_ips\": [],\n85:             \"top_dst_ips\": [],\n86:             \"top_src_ports\": [],\n87:             \"top_dst_ports\": [],\n88:             \"packets_per_second\": 0.0,\n89:             \"start_time\": \"\",\n90:             \"end_time\": \"\",\n91:             \"message\": \"No packets in file\",\n92:         }\n93: \n94:     protocol_counter: Counter = Counter()\n95:     src_ip_counter: Counter = Counter()\n96:     dst_ip_counter: Counter = Counter()\n97:     src_port_counter: Counter = Counter()\n98:     dst_port_counter: Counter = Counter()\n99: \n100:     timestamps: List[float] = []\n101: \n102:     for packet in packets:\n103:         protocol = get_packet_protocol(packet)\n104:         protocol_counter[protocol] += 1\n105: \n106:         if packet.haslayer(IP):\n107:             ip_layer = packet[IP]\n108:             src_ip_counter[ip_layer.src] += 1\n109:             dst_ip_counter[ip_layer.dst] += 1\n110: \n111:         if packet.haslayer(TCP) or packet.haslayer(UDP):\n112:             if packet.haslayer(TCP):\n113:                 transport_layer = packet[TCP]\n114:             else:\n115:                 transport_layer = packet[UDP]\n116: \n117:             src_port_counter[transport_layer.sport] += 1\n118:             dst_port_counter[transport_layer.dport] += 1\n119: \n120:         if hasattr(packet, \"time\") and packet.time is not None:\n121:             timestamps.append(float(packet.time))\n122: \n123:     total_packets = len(packets)\n124: \n125:     duration_seconds = 0.0\n126:     start_time = \"\"\n127:     end_time = \"\"\n128:     packets_per_second = 0.0\n129: \n130:     if timestamps:\n131:         min_time = min(timestamps)\n132:         max_time = max(timestamps)\n133:         duration_seconds = max_time - min_time\n134:         start_time = datetime.fromtimestamp(min_time).isoformat()\n135:         end_time = datetime.fromtimestamp(max_time).isoformat()\n136: \n137:         if duration_seconds > 0:\n138:             packets_per_second = total_packets / duration_seconds\n139: \n140:     return {\n141:         \"total_packets\": total_packets,\n142:         \"duration_seconds\": round(duration_seconds, 3),\n143:         \"protocols\": dict(protocol_counter),\n144:         \"top_src_ips\": [],\n145:         \"top_dst_ips\": [],\n146:         \"top_src_ports\": [],\n147:         \"top_dst_ports\": [],\n148:         \"packets_per_second\": round(packets_per_second, 3),\n149:         \"start_time\": start_time,\n150:         \"end_time\": end_time,\n151:         \"_src_ip_counter\": src_ip_counter,\n152:         \"_dst_ip_counter\": dst_ip_counter,\n153:         \"_src_port_counter\": src_port_counter,\n154:         \"_dst_port_counter\": dst_port_counter,\n155:     }\n156: \n157: \n158: def get_top_n(\n159:     counter: Counter, n: int\n160: ) -> List[Tuple[str, int]]:\n161:     \"\"\"Get top N items from a counter.\n162: \n163:     Args:\n164:         counter: Counter object with counts\n165:         n: Number of top items to return\n166: \n167:     Returns:\n168:         List of (item, count) tuples\n169:     \"\"\"\n170:     return counter.most_common(n)\n171: \n172: \n173: def format_text_output(result: Dict[str, Any], top_n: int) -> str:\n174:     \"\"\"Format analysis results as text.\n175: \n176:     Args:\n177:         result: Analysis results dictionary\n178:         top_n: Number of top items to display\n179: \n180:     Returns:\n181:         Formatted text string\n182:     \"\"\"\n183:     lines = []\n184:     lines.append(\"=\" * 60)\n185:     lines.append(\"PCAP Analysis Report\")\n186:     lines.append(\"=\" * 60)\n187:     lines.append(\"\")\n188: \n189:     lines.append(f\"Total Packets: {result['total_packets']}\")\n190: \n191:     if result.get(\"message\"):\n192:         lines.append(f\"Note: {result['message']}\")\n193:         return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n194: \n195:     lines.append(f\"Duration: {result['duration_seconds']:.3f} seconds\")\n196:     lines.append(f\"Start Time: {result['start_time']}\")\n197:     lines.append(f\"End Time: {result['end_time']}\")\n198:     lines.append(f\"Packets per Second: {result['packets_per_second']:.3f}\")\n199:     lines.append(\"\")\n200: \n201:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n202:     lines.append(\"Protocol Distribution\")\n203:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n204: \n205:     total = result[\"total_packets\"]\n206:     for protocol, count in sorted(result[\"protocols\"].items(), key=lambda x: -x[1]):\n207:         percentage = (count / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0\n208:         lines.append(f\"  {protocol}: {count} ({percentage:.1f}%)\")\n209: \n210:     lines.append(\"\")\n211:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n212:     lines.append(f\"Top {top_n} Source IPs\")\n213:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n214: \n215:     src_ip_counter = result.get(\"_src_ip_counter\", Counter())\n216:     for ip, count in get_top_n(src_ip_counter, top_n):\n217:         lines.append(f\"  {ip}: {count}\")\n218: \n219:     lines.append(\"\")\n220:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n221:     lines.append(f\"Top {top_n} Destination IPs\")\n222:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n223: \n224:     dst_ip_counter = result.get(\"_dst_ip_counter\", Counter())\n225:     for ip, count in get_top_n(dst_ip_counter, top_n):\n226:         lines.append(f\"  {ip}: {count}\")\n227: \n228:     lines.append(\"\")\n229:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n230:     lines.append(f\"Top {top_n} Source Ports\")\n231:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n232: \n233:     src_port_counter = result.get(\"_src_port_counter\", Counter())\n234:     for port, count in get_top_n(src_port_counter, top_n):\n235:         lines.append(f\"  {port}: {count}\")\n236: \n237:     lines.append(\"\")\n238:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n239:     lines.append(f\"Top {top_n} Destination Ports\")\n240:     lines.append(\"-\" * 60)\n241: \n242:     dst_port_counter = result.get(\"_dst_port_counter\", Counter())\n243:     for port, count in get_top_n(dst_port_counter, top_n):\n244:         lines.append(f\"  {port}: {count}\")\n245: \n246:     lines.append(\"\")\n247:     lines.append(\"=\" * 60)\n248: \n249:     return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n250: \n251: \n252: def format_json_output(result: Dict[str, Any], top_n: int) -> str:\n253:     \"\"\"Format analysis results as JSON.\n254: \n255:     Args:\n256:         result: Analysis results dictionary\n257:         top_n: Number of top items to include\n258: \n259:     Returns:\n260:         JSON formatted string\n261:     \"\"\"\n262:     if result.get(\"message\"):\n263:         output = {\n264:             \"total_packets\": result[\"total_packets\"],\n265:             \"message\": result[\"message\"],\n266:         }\n267:         return json.dumps(output, indent=2)\n268: \n269:     output = {\n270:         \"total_packets\": result[\"total_packets\"],\n271:         \"duration_seconds\": result[\"duration_seconds\"],\n272:         \"protocols\": result[\"protocols\"],\n273:         \"top_src_ips\": get_top_n(result.get(\"_src_ip_counter\", Counter()), top_n),\n274:         \"top_dst_ips\": get_top_n(result.get(\"_dst_ip_counter\", Counter()), top_n),\n275:         \"top_src_ports\": [\n276:             (int(port), count)\n277:             for port, count in get_top_n(result.get(\"_src_port_counter\", Counter()), top_n)\n278:         ],\n279:         \"top_dst_ports\": [\n280:             (int(port), count)\n281:             for port, count in get_top_n(result.get(\"_dst_port_counter\", Counter()), top_n)\n282:         ],\n283:         \"packets_per_second\": result[\"packets_per_second\"],\n284:         \"start_time\": result[\"start_time\"],\n285:         \"end_time\": result[\"end_time\"],\n286:     }\n287: \n288:     return json.dumps(output, indent=2)\n289: \n290: \n291: def analyze_pcap_file(\n292:     file_path: str,\n293:     top_n: int = 10,\n294:     output_format: str = \"text\",\n295:     verbose: bool = False,\n296: ) -> str:\n297:     \"\"\"Main function to analyze a PCAP file.\n298: \n299:     Args:\n300:         file_path: Path to the PCAP file\n301:         top_n: Number of top items to return\n302:         output_format: Output format ('text' or 'json')\n303:         verbose: Enable verbose output\n304: \n305:     Returns:\n306:         Formatted analysis results\n307: \n308:     Raises:\n309:         FileNotFoundError: If the PCAP file does not exist\n310:         PcapAnalysisError: If analysis fails\n311:     \"\"\"\n312:     if verbose:\n313:         print(f\"Loading PCAP file: {file_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n314: \n315:     packets = parse_pcap(file_path)\n316: \n317:     if verbose:\n318:         print(f\"Loaded {len(packets)} packets\", file=sys.stderr)\n319:         print(\"Analyzing packets...\", file=sys.stderr)\n320: \n321:     result = analyze_packets(packets)\n322: \n323:     if verbose:\n324:         print(\"Analysis complete\", file=sys.stderr)\n325: \n326:     if output_format == \"json\":\n327:         return format_json_output(result, top_n)\n328:     else:\n329:         return format_text_output(result, top_n)\n330: \n331: \n332: @app.command()\n333: def main(\n334:     file: str = typer.Option(\n335:         ..., \"--file\", \"-f\", help=\"Path to the PCAP file to analyze\"\n336:     ),\n337:     top_n: int = typer.Option(\n338:         10, \"--top-n\", \"-n\", help=\"Number of top IPs/ports to display\"\n339:     ),\n340:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n341:         None, \"--output\", \"-o\", help=\"Output file path (default: stdout)\"\n342:     ),\n343:     format: str = typer.Option(\n344:         \"text\", \"--format\", help=\"Output format: text or json\"\n345:     ),\n346:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n347:         False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"\n348:     ),\n349: ) -> None:\n350:     \"\"\"Analyze PCAP files and extract network traffic statistics.\n351: \n352:     This tool parses PCAP files and provides statistics including:\n353:     - Total packet count\n354:     - Protocol distribution\n355:     - Top source/destination IPs\n356:     - Top source/destination ports\n357:     - Traffic time range and rate\n358:     \"\"\"\n359:     if format not in (\"text\", \"json\"):\n360:         typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid format '{format}'. Must be 'text' or 'json'\")\n361:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n362: \n363:     try:\n364:         result = analyze_pcap_file(\n365:             file_path=file,\n366:             top_n=top_n,\n367:             output_format=format,\n368:             verbose=verbose,\n369:         )\n370: \n371:         if output:\n372:             output_path = Path(output)\n373:             output_path.write_text(result)\n374:             if verbose:\n375:                 typer.echo(f\"Results written to: {output}\", err=True)\n376:         else:\n377:             typer.echo(result)\n378: \n379:     except FileNotFoundError as e:\n380:         typer.echo(f\"Error: {e}\", err=True)\n381:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n382:     except PcapAnalysisError as e:\n383:         typer.echo(f\"Error: {e}\", err=True)\n384:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n385: \n386: \n387: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n388:     app()\n\n(End of file - total 388 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"PCAP Analyzer - Parse PCAP files and extract network traffic statistics.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom collections import Counter\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\n\nimport typer\nfrom scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, rdpcap\nfrom scapy.layers.http import HTTPRequest, HTTPResponse\n\napp = typer.Typer()\n\n\nclass PcapAnalysisError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for PCAP analysis errors.\"\"\"\n\n    pass","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer.py","time":{"start":1775887658484,"end":1775887658508}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887658513,"sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b272377001rL3RcH4Ww1stLG","messageID":"msg_d7b2711b4001lhAz91H4OoUalX","sessionID":"ses_284d9a927ffeKmL6b3rSnSwlEg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_51c748af98504628a91f9806","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer_agent.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer_agent.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer with AgentCube SDK Integration Example.\n2: \n3: This example demonstrates how to use the AgentCube SDK to execute\n4: PCAP analysis in a remote code interpreter environment.\n5: \"\"\"\n6: \n7: import os\n8: from typing import Optional\n9: \n10: try:\n11:     from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n12: except ImportError:\n13:     CodeInterpreterClient = None\n14: \n15: \n16: class PcapAnalyzerAgent:\n17:     \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer using AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient.\n18: \n19:     This class provides a high-level interface for analyzing PCAP files\n20:     using the AgentCube SDK. It handles file upload, code execution,\n21:     and result retrieval.\n22: \n23:     Attributes:\n24:         namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n25:         router_url: Router base URL\n26:         workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n27:         verbose: Enable verbose logging\n28:     \"\"\"\n29: \n30:     ANALYZER_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\n31: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP\n32: from scapy.layers.http import HTTPRequest, HTTPResponse\n33: from collections import Counter\n34: from datetime import datetime\n35: import json\n36: \n37: def get_protocol(packet):\n38:     if packet.haslayer(HTTPRequest):\n39:         return \"HTTP\"\n40:     elif packet.haslayer(HTTPResponse):\n41:         return \"HTTP\"\n42:     elif packet.haslayer(TCP):\n43:         return \"TCP\"\n44:     elif packet.haslayer(UDP):\n45:         return \"UDP\"\n46:     elif packet.haslayer(IP):\n47:         return \"IP\"\n48:     else:\n49:         return \"OTHER\"\n50: \n51: def analyze_pcap(file_path, top_n=10):\n52:     packets = rdpcap(file_path)\n53:     total = len(packets)\n54: \n55:     if total == 0:\n56:         return {{\n57:             \"total_packets\": 0,\n58:             \"message\": \"No packets in file\"\n59:         }}\n60: \n61:     protocols = Counter()\n62:     src_ips = Counter()\n63:     dst_ips = Counter()\n64:     src_ports = Counter()\n65:     dst_ports = Counter()\n66:     timestamps = []\n67: \n68:     for pkt in packets:\n69:         protocols[get_protocol(pkt)] += 1\n70: \n71:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n72:             src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n73:             dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n74: \n75:         if pkt.haslayer(TCP) or pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n76:             layer = pkt[TCP] if pkt.haslayer(TCP) else pkt[UDP]\n77:             src_ports[layer.sport] += 1\n78:             dst_ports[layer.dport] += 1\n79: \n80:         if hasattr(pkt, 'time'):\n81:             timestamps.append(float(pkt.time))\n82: \n83:     duration = 0.0\n84:     start_time = \"\"\n85:     end_time = \"\"\n86:     pps = 0.0\n87: \n88:     if timestamps:\n89:         min_t = min(timestamps)\n90:         max_t = max(timestamps)\n91:         duration = max_t - min_t\n92:         start_time = datetime.fromtimestamp(min_t).isoformat()\n93:         end_time = datetime.fromtimestamp(max_t).isoformat()\n94:         if duration > 0:\n95:             pps = total / duration\n96: \n97:     result = {{\n98:         \"total_packets\": total,\n99:         \"duration_seconds\": round(duration, 3),\n100:         \"protocols\": dict(protocols),\n101:         \"top_src_ips\": src_ips.most_common(top_n),\n102:         \"top_dst_ips\": dst_ips.most_common(top_n),\n103:         \"top_src_ports\": [(int(p), c) for p, c in src_ports.most_common(top_n)],\n104:         \"top_dst_ports\": [(int(p), c) for p, c in dst_ports.most_common(top_n)],\n105:         \"packets_per_second\": round(pps, 3),\n106:         \"start_time\": start_time,\n107:         \"end_time\": end_time,\n108:     }}\n109: \n110:     return result\n111: \n112: result = analyze_pcap(\"{file_path}\", {top_n})\n113: print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n114: \"\"\"\n115: \n116:     def __init__(\n117:         self,\n118:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n119:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n120:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n121:         verbose: bool = False,\n122:     ) -> None:\n123:         \"\"\"Initialize PcapAnalyzerAgent.\n124: \n125:         Args:\n126:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n127:             router_url: Router base URL (or ROUTER_URL env var)\n128:             workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL (or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var)\n129:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n130:         \"\"\"\n131:         self.namespace = namespace\n132:         self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n133:         self.workload_manager_url = workload_manager_url or os.getenv(\n134:             \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"\n135:         )\n136:         self.verbose = verbose\n137: \n138:     def analyze(\n139:         self,\n140:         pcap_file_path: str,\n141:         top_n: int = 10,\n142:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n143:     ) -> dict:\n144:         \"\"\"Analyze a PCAP file using CodeInterpreterClient.\n145: \n146:         This method:\n147:         1. Reads the local PCAP file\n148:         2. Uploads it to the code interpreter session\n149:         3. Executes the analysis script\n150:         4. Parses and returns the JSON result\n151: \n152:         Args:\n153:             pcap_file_path: Path to the local PCAP file\n154:             top_n: Number of top items to return\n155:             timeout: Optional execution timeout in seconds\n156: \n157:         Returns:\n158:             Dictionary containing analysis results\n159: \n160:         Raises:\n161:             FileNotFoundError: If the PCAP file does not exist\n162:             RuntimeError: If analysis fails\n163:         \"\"\"\n164:         import os as local_os\n165: \n166:         if not local_os.path.exists(pcap_file_path):\n167:             raise FileNotFoundError(f\"PCAP file not found: {pcap_file_path}\")\n168: \n169:         with CodeInterpreterClient(\n170:             namespace=self.namespace,\n171:             router_url=self.router_url,\n172:             workload_manager_url=self.workload_manager_url,\n173:             verbose=self.verbose,\n174:         ) as client:\n175:             with open(pcap_file_path, \"rb\") as f:\n176:                 file_content = f.read()\n177: \n178:             remote_filename = \"capture.pcap\"\n179:             client.upload_file(remote_filename, file_content)\n180: \n181:             script = self.ANALYZER_SCRIPT.format(\n182:                 file_path=remote_filename, top_n=top_n\n183:             )\n184: \n185:             result = client.execute(script, timeout=timeout)\n186: \n187:             output = result.get(\"output\", \"\")\n188: \n189:             try:\n190:                 start_idx = output.find(\"{\")\n191:                 end_idx = output.rfind(\"}\") + 1\n192:                 if start_idx >= 0 and end_idx > start_idx:\n193:                     json_str = output[start_idx:end_idx]\n194:                     return json.loads(json_str)\n195:                 else:\n196:                     return json.loads(output)\n197:             except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n198:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to parse analysis result: {e}\")\n199: \n200:     def analyze_from_bytes(\n201:         self,\n202:         pcap_content: bytes,\n203:         top_n: int = 10,\n204:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n205:     ) -> dict:\n206:         \"\"\"Analyze PCAP data from bytes.\n207: \n208:         This method:\n209:         1. Uploads the PCAP content directly\n210:         2. Executes the analysis script\n211:         3. Parses and returns the JSON result\n212: \n213:         Args:\n214:             pcap_content: PCAP file content as bytes\n215:             top_n: Number of top items to return\n216:             timeout: Optional execution timeout in seconds\n217: \n218:         Returns:\n219:             Dictionary containing analysis results\n220: \n221:         Raises:\n222:             RuntimeError: If analysis fails\n223:         \"\"\"\n224:         with CodeInterpreterClient(\n225:             namespace=self.namespace,\n226:             router_url=self.router_url,\n227:             workload_manager_url=self.workload_manager_url,\n228:             verbose=self.verbose,\n229:         ) as client:\n230:             remote_filename = \"capture.pcap\"\n231:             client.upload_file(remote_filename, pcap_content)\n232: \n233:             script = self.ANALYZER_SCRIPT.format(\n234:                 file_path=remote_filename, top_n=top_n\n235:             )\n236: \n237:             result = client.execute(script, timeout=timeout)\n238: \n239:             output = result.get(\"output\", \"\")\n240: \n241:             try:\n242:                 start_idx = output.find(\"{\")\n243:                 end_idx = output.rfind(\"}\") + 1\n244:                 if start_idx >= 0 and end_idx > start_idx:\n245:                     json_str = output[start_idx:end_idx]\n246:                     return json.loads(json_str)\n247:                 else:\n248:                     return json.loads(output)\n249:             except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n250:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to parse analysis result: {e}\")\n251: \n252: \n253: def main():\n254:     \"\"\"Example usage of PcapAnalyzerAgent.\"\"\"\n255:     import sys\n256: \n257:     if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n258:         print(\"Usage: python pcap_analyzer_agent.py <pcap_file>\")\n259:         sys.exit(1)\n260: \n261:     pcap_file = sys.argv[1]\n262: \n263:     analyzer = PcapAnalyzerAgent(verbose=True)\n264: \n265:     try:\n266:         result = analyzer.analyze(pcap_file)\n267:         print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n268:     except FileNotFoundError as e:\n269:         print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n270:         sys.exit(1)\n271:     except RuntimeError as e:\n272:         print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n273:         sys.exit(1)\n274: \n275: \n276: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n277:     import json\n278: \n279:     main()\n\n(End of file - total 279 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"PCAP Analyzer with AgentCube SDK Integration Example.\n\nThis example demonstrates how to use the AgentCube SDK to execute\nPCAP analysis in a remote code interpreter environment.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional\n\ntry:\n    from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nexcept ImportError:\n    CodeInterpreterClient = None\n\n\nclass PcapAnalyzerAgent:\n    \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer using AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient.\n\n    This class provides a high-level interface for analyzing PCAP files\n    using the AgentCube SDK. It handles file upload, code execution,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/examples/pcap_analyzer_agent.py","time":{"start":1775887658487,"end":1775887658510}}}}
